**Audit complete.** Report created at `docs/audit/ielts-journey-ui-ux-audit-report.md` (397 lines).

**Key findings (13 sections):**

1. **Routes/Navigation**: Leading border on active menu items (Layout.tsx:261), `/progress-review` duplicates `/progress`, 4+ dead/unused page files
2. **Page Headers**: No shared `PageHeader` component exists. 10+ pages missing title icons — Mistake Review, Today Plan, Progress, Settings, Vocabulary, Dashboard all lack proper headers
3. **Containers**: No shared `PageContainer` — each page uses different max-width (896px/1200px/1280px), inconsistent padding
4. **Color Overuse**: 6+ locations with overly colorful cards/badges (extension stat cards, skill badges in mistake pages, per-action colors in selected text menu)
5. **Duplicate Pages**: `pages/Mistakes.tsx` (859 lines) is dead code; `ListeningJournal.tsx` (886 lines) and `ReadingJournal.tsx` (853 lines) are unused/duplicate
6. **Duplicate Components**: Two `BottomNavigation` implementations (ui package + local), extension duplicates all theme CSS tokens
7. **Fake Features**: "Ask AI" button in Today Plan (setTimeout with no real action), "View Progress" has empty onClick
8. **AI Tutor**: Incomplete page-level implementation, Headbar button uses transparent/light background
9. **Mixed Imports**: Some pages use local `../../components/ui/` while others use `@ielts/ui` — both reference the same component types
10. **Missing Word Family**: Vocabulary notebook imports `WordFamilyDisplay` but expand/dropdown UI is not functional per task description
11. **Chat Container**: Width/wrapping issues likely from ChatPopup component
12. **Extension**: Duplicate CSS tokens, no dark mode toggling, colorful stat cards at small popup size
13. **19 priority fixes** identified with severity levels
